Title: Very Rare Vintage Omega De Ville Chronograph movement 860. Ref:145.017
Description: You are bidding on the very rare Caliber 860 movement only 10,000 were produced in it's run compared to the 300,000 plus for the Caliber 861. This watch has a nice warm patina and is in good running condition. I would suggest a servicing the watch, in fine condition. Steel Omega De Ville Ref. 145.017 vintage wristwatch. A handsome stainless steel manually wound chronograph wristwatch with register and tachymeter Omega introduced Ref.145.017 in 1968. The classic silvered dial has applied indexes and two subsidiary dials for constant seconds to the left and, to the right, a 30-minute register to record time elapsed when the chronograph is running. The chronograph can be both started and stopped by the upper pusher and reset via the lower pusher. The outer tachymeter scale is designed to measure the speed of a travelling object over a set distance. Technical Details: Omega calibre 860 manually wound movement, lever escapement, 17 jewels, mono-metallic balance, 21,600 BPH, incabloc shock absorber silvered dial, applied baton numerals, two engine-turned subsidiary dials for constant seconds and 30-minute register, outer scale calibrated for tachymeter with track for minutes/chronograph seconds beneath; polished stainless steel case with satin finished back, Omega winding crown; case, dial, movement and crown signed.
